Enumeration Type Documentation

enum Codes
 

Http response codes.

Enumeration values:
OK  The request was fulfilled.
FOUND  The data resides under a different URL.

The redirection may be altered on occasion.

SEE_OTHER  The response to the request can be found under another URI.
NOT_MODIFIED  If the client has performed a conditional GET request and access is allowed, but the document has not been modified, the server SHOULD respond with this status code.
BAD_REQUEST  The request had bad syntax or was inherently impossible to be satisfied.
FORBIDDEN  The request is for something forbidden.
NOT_FOUND  The server encountered an unexpected condition which prevented it from fulfilling the request.
METHOD_NOT_ALLOWED  The method specified in the Request-Line is not allowed for the resource identified by the Request-URI.
GONE  The requested resource is no longer available at the server and no forwarding address is known.
REQUEST_ENTITY_TOO_LARGE  The request is larger than the server is willing or able to process.
REQUEST_URI_TOO_LONG  The URI provied was too long for the server to process.
EXPECTATION_FAILED  The server cannot meet the requirements of the Expected request-header field.
IM_A_TEAPOT  The HTCPCP server is a teapot.
INTERNAL_ERROR  A generica error message, give when no more specific message is suitable.
NOT_IMPLEMENTED  The server either does not recognise the request method, or it lacks the ability to fulfil the request.
SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE  The server is currently unavailable, this is a temporary state.
HTTP_VERSION_NOT_SUPPORTED  The server does not support the HTTP protocol version used in the request.
